<subSubSection box="[189,550,1294,1321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,935,1934]" box="[189,550,1294,1321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,550,1294,1321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Doweld" authorityName="Doweld" authorityYear="1999" box="[266,545,1295,1321]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Tephrocacteae">Tephrocacteae Doweld</taxonomicName>
:
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,935,1934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
—According to phylogenetic analyses (
<bibRefCitation author="Ritz, C. M. &amp; Reiker, J. &amp; Charles, G. &amp; Hoxey, P. &amp; Hunt, D. &amp; Lowry, M. &amp; Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N." box="[1014,1207,1295,1321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="668 - 681" refId="ref18513" refString="Ritz, C. M., Reiker, J., Charles, G., Hoxey, P., Hunt, D., Lowry, M., Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N. (2012) Molecular phylogeny and character evolution in terete - stemmed Andean opuntias (Cactaceae - Opuntioideae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 668 - 681. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2012.07.027" type="journal article" year="2012">
Ritz 
<emphasis box="[1075,1136,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, J. &amp; Yang, Y. &amp; Feng, T. &amp; Timoneda, A. &amp; Mikenas, J. &amp; Hutchison, V. &amp; Edwards, C. &amp; Wang, N. &amp; Ahluwalia, S. &amp; Olivieri, J. &amp; Walker-Hale, N. &amp; Majure, L. C. &amp; Puente, R. &amp; Kadereit, G. &amp; Lauterbach, M. &amp; Eggli, U. &amp; Flores-Olvera, H. &amp; Ochoterena, H. &amp; Brockington, S. F. &amp; Moore, M. J. &amp; Smith, S. A." box="[1223,1447,1295,1321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="446 - 462" refId="ref19150" refString="Walker, J. F, Yang, Y., Feng, T., Timoneda, A., Mikenas, J., Hutchison, V., Edwards, C., Wang, N., Ahluwalia, S., Olivieri, J., Walker-Hale, N., Majure, L. C., Puente, R., Kadereit, G., Lauterbach, M., Eggli, U., Flores-Olvera, H., Ochoterena, H., Brockington, S. F., Moore, M. J. &amp; Smith, S. A. (2018) From cacti to carnivores: improved phylotranscriptomic sampling and hierarchical homology inference provide further insight into the evolution of Caryophyllales. American Journal of Botany 105: 446 - 462. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / ajb 2.1069" type="journal article" year="2018">
Walker 
<emphasis box="[1315,1376,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Majure, L. C. &amp; Baker, M. A. &amp; Cloud-Hughes, M. &amp; Salywon, A. &amp; Neubig, K. M." box="[136,354,1331,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="1327 - 1345" refId="ref18018" refString="Majure, L. C., Baker, M. A., Cloud-Hughes, M., Salywon, A. &amp; Neubig, K. M. (2019) Phylogenomics in Cactaceae: A case study using the chollas sensu lato (Cylindropuntieae, Opuntioideae) reveals a common pattern out of the Chihuahuan and Sonoran deserts. American Journal of Botany 106: 1327 - 1345. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / ajb 2.1364" type="journal article" year="2019">
Majure 
<emphasis box="[226,285,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
), the monophyletic clade “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doweld" authorityYear="1999" box="[660,828,1331,1357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Tephrocacteae">Tephrocacteae</taxonomicName>
” represents a widely distributed group which includes the genera 
<taxonomicName authority="K. Schum." authorityName="K. Schum." box="[271,529,1367,1393]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Pterocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[271,404,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pterocactus</emphasis>
K.Schum.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Speg." authorityName="Speg." box="[549,790,1367,1393]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[549,714,1367,1393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
Speg.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lem." authorityName="Lem." box="[810,1033,1367,1393]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Tephrocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,959,1367,1393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Tephrocactus</emphasis>
Lem.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Backeb." authorityName="Backeb." box="[1049,1394,1367,1393]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Austrocylindropuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1049,1286,1367,1393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Austrocylindropuntia</emphasis>
Backeb.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="F. Ritter. The" authorityName="F. Ritter. The" box="[136,442,1403,1429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Cumulopuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,296,1403,1429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cumulopuntia</emphasis>
F.Ritter. The
</taxonomicName>
study by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritz, C. M. &amp; Reiker, J. &amp; Charles, G. &amp; Hoxey, P. &amp; Hunt, D. &amp; Lowry, M. &amp; Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N." box="[550,740,1403,1429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="668 - 681" refId="ref18513" refString="Ritz, C. M., Reiker, J., Charles, G., Hoxey, P., Hunt, D., Lowry, M., Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N. (2012) Molecular phylogeny and character evolution in terete - stemmed Andean opuntias (Cactaceae - Opuntioideae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 668 - 681. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2012.07.027" type="journal article" year="2012">
Ritz 
<emphasis box="[603,659,1403,1429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
retrieved two main clades, one of which comprises 
<taxonomicName box="[1319,1452,1404,1429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Pterocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1319,1452,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pterocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[181,346,1439,1465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,346,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other one harbours 
<taxonomicName box="[646,795,1439,1465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Tephrocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[646,795,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Tephrocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the sister pair 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1157,1439,1465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Cumulopuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[997,1157,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cumulopuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1207,1444,1439,1465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Austrocylindropuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1207,1444,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Austrocylindropuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Former taxonomic concepts (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. &amp; Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G." box="[517,706,1475,1501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" refId="ref17156" refString="Hunt, D., Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G. (2006) The New Cactus Lexicon. DH Books, Milborn Port, 526 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Hunt 
<emphasis box="[581,638,1475,1501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
: p. 12) suggested a close relationship between 
<taxonomicName box="[1238,1403,1475,1501]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1238,1403,1475,1501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[136,296,1511,1537]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Cumulopuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,296,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cumulopuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly for their shared gross morphology. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wallace, R. S. &amp; Dickie, S. L." box="[770,1065,1511,1537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="9 - 24" refId="ref19103" refString="Wallace, R. S. &amp; Dickie, S. L. (2002) Systematic implications of chloroplast DNA sequence variation in subfam. Opuntioideae (Cactaceae) Studies in the Opuntieae (Cactaceae). Succulent Plant Research 6: 9 - 24." type="journal article" year="2002">Wallace &amp; Dickie’s (2002)</bibRefCitation>
results suggest a close relationship between 
<taxonomicName box="[239,404,1547,1573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[239,404,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[463,628,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Thephrocactus</emphasis>
and, furthermore, 
<taxonomicName box="[845,978,1548,1573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Pterocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[845,978,1548,1573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pterocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated as a tribe, an opinion shared by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U." box="[173,455,1583,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref18353" refString="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U. (2010) A farewell to dated ideas and concepts: molecular phylogenetics and a revised suprageneric classification of the family Cactaceae. Schumannia 6: 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2010">Nyffeler &amp; Eggli (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. Yet, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffith, M. P. &amp; Porter, J. M." box="[551,831,1583,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="107 - 116" refId="ref16665" refString="Griffith, M. P. &amp; Porter, J. M. (2009) Phylogeny of Opuntioideae (Cactaceae). International Journal of Plant Science 170: 107 - 116. https: // doi. org / 10.1086 / 593048" type="journal article" year="2009">Griffith &amp; Porter (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[845,978,1584,1609]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Pterocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[845,978,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pterocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not isolated but was placed together with 
<taxonomicName box="[195,360,1619,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[195,360,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a basal grade to the rest of the terete-stemmed 
<taxonomicName box="[941,1096,1619,1645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Opuntioideae">Opuntioideae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritz, C. M. &amp; Reiker, J. &amp; Charles, G. &amp; Hoxey, P. &amp; Hunt, D. &amp; Lowry, M. &amp; Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N." box="[1108,1306,1619,1645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="668 - 681" refId="ref18513" refString="Ritz, C. M., Reiker, J., Charles, G., Hoxey, P., Hunt, D., Lowry, M., Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N. (2012) Molecular phylogeny and character evolution in terete - stemmed Andean opuntias (Cactaceae - Opuntioideae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 668 - 681. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2012.07.027" type="journal article" year="2012">
Ritz 
<emphasis box="[1164,1222,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName box="[136,269,1656,1681]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Pterocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,269,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pterocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not isolated, appearing as sister to 
<taxonomicName box="[702,867,1655,1681]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[702,867,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This finding supports Stuppy’s (2001) assumption that the genus might be closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[601,766,1691,1717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[601,766,1691,1717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although some morphological characters of 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1411,1692,1717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Pterocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1411,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pterocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unique in the tribe and the 
<taxonomicName box="[430,581,1727,1753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Opuntioideae">Opuntioideae</taxonomicName>
(the base of the glochids is rounded; the flowers are immersed into the apex of the segment; at an early oncological stage the fruit is not clearly separated from the surrounding tissue of the segment; the funicular girdle of the seed forms a broad papery and undulating wing), it shares some important morphological characters with 
<taxonomicName box="[320,485,1835,1861]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Maihueniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[320,485,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Maihueniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to all these findings our classification follows the results of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritz, C. M. &amp; Reiker, J. &amp; Charles, G. &amp; Hoxey, P. &amp; Hunt, D. &amp; Lowry, M. &amp; Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N." pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="668 - 681" refId="ref18513" refString="Ritz, C. M., Reiker, J., Charles, G., Hoxey, P., Hunt, D., Lowry, M., Stuppy, W. &amp; Taylor, N. (2012) Molecular phylogeny and character evolution in terete - stemmed Andean opuntias (Cactaceae - Opuntioideae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 668 - 681. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2012.07.027" type="journal article" year="2012">
Ritz 
<emphasis box="[1392,1452,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
. According to the results of Ritz 
<emphasis box="[597,655,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
one large species-complex was split: 
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1366,1871,1897]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Cumulopuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boliviana">
<emphasis box="[1091,1366,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Cumulopuntia boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Salm-Dyck) F.Ritter (
